# Quote / order form delivery
#
# The order form can deliver requests straight to your inbox so you don't rely on
# the visitor's email client. It uses Web3Forms (https://web3forms.com), a free
# service that works on static hosts like GitHub Pages.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Go to https://web3forms.com, enter the email where you want to receive
#      quote requests, and copy the generated Access Key.
#   2. Set the value below (in a local .env file, or as a build-time variable /
#      repository secret in your GitHub Pages workflow).
#
# Notes:
#   - This key is a public submission token, safe to expose in the built site.
#     It only allows sending to the address you configured. Your address is not
#     used by the primary delivery path (the service holds it), though it remains
#     embedded for the mailto: fallback used if the service is unreachable.
#   - If this is left empty, the form falls back to opening the visitor's own
#     email client (mailto:), exactly like before.
PUBLIC_WEB3FORMS_KEY=
